  "title": "Project Engineer (Construction, M&E)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Oversee contract execution and monitor installation progress, ensuring timely delivery through coordination with clients, consultants, and subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and review method statements, shop drawings, technical submissions, and work progress reports for M&amp;E-related tasks.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with stakeholders to resolve technical and site issues, and coordinate with authorities for inspections, testing, and commissioning.</li>\n  <li>Assist in procurement of materials, equipment, and labour within budget while supporting project negotiations.</li>\n  <li>Apply expertise in Data Centers, DfMA, and specialized systems such as VAV/VRV, chillers, chilled water pipes, and lighting control systems.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience handling and monitoring the progress of projects in <strong>Construction industry.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
